My name is Diyauddin Shaik, and I have around 4 years of experience as a Cloud DevOps Engineer at TCS. My core experience is in AWS cloud infrastructure, CI/CD automation, monitoring, and security compliance.

I started my career with a data platform project built on Hadoop and MapR, where the system handled large-scale enterprise data for analytics and reporting. My role was to maintain cluster stability, 
troubleshoot job failures, and monitor system performance using tools like Prometheus and Grafana. This gave me strong experience in Linux, monitoring, and platform reliability.

Currently, I am working on the Ericsson R&D project, which provides a cloud-based DevOps platform for telecom microservices. These microservices support telecom operations such as service routing, analytics, 
and monitoring, and they are deployed as containerized applications.

The platform runs across both AWS Commercial (COM) and AWS GovCloud (GOV) environments. COM is mainly used for development and testing workloads, 
while GOV is used for secure workloads that require strict compliance standards.

Infrastructure is provisioned using Terraform, and we use AWS services like EC2, EKS, S3, IAM, and ECR. Jenkins is used to implement CI/CD pipelines for building and deploying applications into Kubernetes clusters on EKS.
For monitoring and observability, we use Prometheus to collect metrics and Grafana dashboards to monitor system performance and generate alerts.

One of the key requirements is maintaining a highly secure environment, especially in GovCloud. I worked on vulnerability remediation tasks, 
fixing issues identified by security scans such as missing security headers like HSTS and clickjacking protection, and ensuring compliance with standards like FedRAMP.

I also worked on automation using AWS Lambda to handle operational workflows such as data processing and alert handling, which reduced manual effort.

On a daily basis, I handle requests related to infrastructure provisioning, CI/CD pipeline troubleshooting, access management, and security remediation. 
I analyze the issue, identify the root cause, implement the solution, and ensure the system remains stable.

Overall, our platform enables telecom applications to run securely and reliably, while allowing development teams to deploy faster using DevOps practices.
